1
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:52,458
♪

2
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:54,166
[GIRL 1]
So, did you hear?

3
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:57,041
They totally built this school
on top of some old graveyard.

4
00:01:58,208 --> 00:01:59,833
[GIRL 2]
I know! Crazy, right?

5
00:01:59,916 --> 00:02:01,958
I thought those
weird rocks on campus were

6
00:02:02,041 --> 00:02:04,375
just for decoration,
but they’re grave markers!

7
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:06,291
-[wind blowing]
-[GIRL 3] Ew, stop it!

8
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:08,166
I hate creepy stuff!

9
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:10,291
Seriously, I’m freaking out!

10
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:12,583
[GIRL 1] You’ll love this.
Did you hear about

11
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:14,375
the second-year guy
the other day?

12
00:02:14,458 --> 00:02:15,666
[GIRL 2]
Uh-uh.

13
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:17,291
He was outside his dormitory

14
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:19,625
when a ghost ran right past him!

15
00:02:19,708 --> 00:02:20,708
That’s crazy!

16
00:02:20,791 --> 00:02:22,208
Stop it, stop it, stop it!

17
00:02:22,291 --> 00:02:23,666
Creepy!

18
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:25,500
[knocking]

19
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:26,750
[gasp]

20
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:27,791
-[whimper]
-[BOTH] Huh?

21
00:02:29,458 --> 00:02:32,458
Lights out, girls.
Stories can wait till tomorrow.

22
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:34,333
Okay, Rei Riku!

23
00:02:34,416 --> 00:02:36,541
Clean up and get to bed.

24
00:02:36,625 --> 00:02:38,083
[GIRLS]
Yes, ma’am.

25
00:02:39,083 --> 00:02:40,875
Have a good night!

26
00:02:40,958 --> 00:02:42,083
[GIRL 4]
Good night.

27
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,916
You, too. Sweet dreams, girls.

28
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,125
[sigh]

29
00:02:46,208 --> 00:02:48,250
[breeze blowing]

30
00:02:51,916 --> 00:02:53,916
[gentle snoring]

31
00:02:54,916 --> 00:02:56,833
[REI]
Lights out at 10:00 PM.

32
00:02:56,916 --> 00:02:59,958
Once again, everyone in
the dorm had a normal day.

33
00:03:00,916 --> 00:03:03,916
♪

34
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:08,916
Just another quiet night.

35
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,916
Another day in this life
of no changes. And yet...

36
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:16,333
No one realizes,

37
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:19,708
the only reason we have
these peaceful days

38
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:22,375
is because he fights
to protect them.

39
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,625
-Meow.
-Hey! [laughing]

40
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:29,000
Meow!

41
00:03:30,416 --> 00:03:31,625
[sigh]

42
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:38,750
In a world so far away,
your voice couldn’t reach it,

43
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,833
closed off from everyone,

44
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,625
he fights for us.

45
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:44,875
Even now.

46
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:47,291
[click]

47
00:03:47,375 --> 00:03:51,333
[bell chimes 12 times]

48
00:03:58,041 --> 00:03:59,125
[laser blast]

49
00:03:59,208 --> 00:04:00,875
[roaring]

50
00:04:00,958 --> 00:04:03,000
[rocks crumbling]

51
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:10,625
[shimmering]

52
00:04:15,416 --> 00:04:18,000
[REI]
He begins his battle anew.

53
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:19,541
All alone.

54
00:04:19,625 --> 00:04:22,541
♪

55
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:26,166
[shimmer]

56
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:29,750
[ZOMBIES groaning]

57
00:04:34,125 --> 00:04:37,375
[ZOMBIE] The treasure
lies in the mausoleum.

58
00:04:37,458 --> 00:04:40,041
Zero. Stage zero.

59
00:04:40,125 --> 00:04:42,375
Open the grave.

60
00:04:42,458 --> 00:04:45,916
Take the treasure! Take it!

61
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:46,958
[groaning continues]

62
00:04:47,041 --> 00:04:49,375
[hissing]

63
00:04:49,458 --> 00:04:51,000
[MAN]
Wanchoi! Come here!

64
00:04:51,083 --> 00:04:52,958
Meow! Meow.

65
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:54,875
[meowing]

66
00:04:56,250 --> 00:04:58,583
It’s okay. We’ll be fine.

67
00:04:58,666 --> 00:04:59,916
[laughing]

68
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,750
-[meow]
-[chuckle]

69
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:04,500
Uh-- Oh.

70
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,416
Day after day with these guys.

71
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,041
They don’t know
when to quit, huh?

72
00:05:09,125 --> 00:05:10,291
[meow]

73
00:05:10,375 --> 00:05:12,041
[ZOMBIE]
Riku.

74
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:14,625
Suigin Riku.

75
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,083
Kill him.

76
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:18,625
Kill him now!

77
00:05:18,708 --> 00:05:21,750
[ZOMBIES screaming, snarling]

78
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:29,666
[ZOMBIES running, groaning]

79
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,166
Oh, well.

80
00:05:35,250 --> 00:05:36,916
Guess I better get started.

81
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,416
Time to thin the herd!

82
00:05:39,583 --> 00:05:41,166
♪

83
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,583
[growling, snarling]

84
00:05:47,708 --> 00:05:50,958
[energy blasts]

85
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:53,791
[pained cries]

86
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:57,083
[grunt]

87
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:00,250
[rumbling]

88
00:06:01,208 --> 00:06:03,458
-[energy blasts]
-[yelling]

89
00:06:03,541 --> 00:06:06,375
-[explosion]
-[ZOMBIES screaming]

90
00:06:06,458 --> 00:06:08,041
[growling]

91
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,875
[crackling energy]

92
00:06:12,958 --> 00:06:14,375
[Suigin]
Geez.

93
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:16,625
How many nights has it been?

94
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:18,833
[bows creaking]

95
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:20,958
[arrows whizzing]

96
00:06:23,250 --> 00:06:24,958
[growling]

97
00:06:25,041 --> 00:06:28,250
Feels like I’ve been protecting
this mausoleum for a lifetime.

98
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,125
-[thud]
-[grunt]

99
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:40,000
[grunting]

100
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,291
[grunting, yelling]

101
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:48,500
One day,

102
00:06:48,583 --> 00:06:50,833
this battle will end.

103
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:53,125
And, when it does...

104
00:06:54,625 --> 00:06:56,833
[meow]

105
00:06:57,791 --> 00:06:59,250
I will.

106
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:03,250
[8-bit video game music]

107
00:07:04,291 --> 00:07:05,333
[gunshot]

108
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:08,250
[cartoony noise]

109
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,041
[triumphant music]

110
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,875
-[powers off]
-Aww!

111
00:07:12,958 --> 00:07:14,291
[bang]

112
00:07:14,375 --> 00:07:16,708
We’re talkin’ to you, nerd!
Better listen!

113
00:07:16,791 --> 00:07:19,375
What kinda loser drags
a computer to the pool?

114
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:20,708
[SUIGIN]
Huh? What?

115
00:07:20,791 --> 00:07:22,083
[BOY 1]
We were askin’ if you’ve seen

116
00:07:22,166 --> 00:07:23,666
-a pink haired girl come by.
-[pool chatter]

117
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:25,208
Is that clear enough for you?

118
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:27,041
[SUIGIN]
I, I haven’t seen her.

119
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:29,708
[BOY 2] Hold up. This is that
kid everyone’s talkin’ about!

120
00:07:29,791 --> 00:07:31,541
The one with a dozen jobs.

121
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:34,166
[BOY 1] You’re the lifeguard,
right? Quit fartin’ around!

122
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:35,625
Actually...

123
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:37,750
I can’t really swim, so...

124
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:38,708
Uh.

125
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,750
-I just clean.
-[meowing]

126
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,208
I have to wait until it closes.

127
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:44,708
-[BOY 1] Oh, I see.
-Meow!

128
00:07:44,791 --> 00:07:47,541
So, what would happen if
the little one fell in?

129
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:48,875
[gasp]
Don’t do it!

130
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:50,083
Meow! Meow! Meow!

131
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:52,000
Better learn to swim and fast!

132
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:54,458
[meowing]

133
00:07:54,541 --> 00:07:56,250
-[splash]
-Wanchoi!

134
00:07:58,125 --> 00:07:59,458
[splash]

135
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:02,375
[choke, gag]

136
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:04,458
[bubbling, gurgling]

137
00:08:07,583 --> 00:08:09,958
There’s no way
I could save him.

138
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:12,833
Why’d I jump in? Why?

139
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:20,500
[groaning]

140
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:21,458
Meow!

141
00:08:21,541 --> 00:08:23,500
Hey.

142
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:25,833
What... happened?

143
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:28,666
-[meowing]
-[laughing]

144
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,125
Wait! Hey!

145
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:31,541
Cut it out, you're tickling me!

146
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:32,708
[MAN]
Finally.

147
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:35,000
-[meowing]
-I thought you were dead.

148
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,000
Suigin.

149
00:08:36,958 --> 00:08:38,250
[shimmer]

150
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:41,083
Ranshou?

151
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:42,458
Meow!

152
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,166
[sweeping]

153
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:50,000
[SUIGIN]
So, you rescued me?

154
00:08:50,083 --> 00:08:52,916
[RANSHOU]
Sadly, no. I got here too late.

155
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,291
When I arrived,
you’d already been pulled out.

156
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:57,208
Rei Riku saved you.

157
00:08:58,500 --> 00:08:59,916
[SUIGIN]
Rei Riku?

158
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:04,416
[RANSHOU] She’s the only
daughter of Yuuki Riku,

159
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:07,041
vice president of
the God Grave Tech Company.

160
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:08,500
♪

161
00:09:08,583 --> 00:09:10,083
-[MEN clamoring]
-She’s got tons of suitors,

162
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:11,708
and apparently had
a 40-foot container

163
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:14,000
filled with presents
for her birthday.

164
00:09:14,958 --> 00:09:17,750
She’s easily the smartest girl
in our school.

165
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:19,208
-[giggle]
-A perfect princess.

166
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:21,125
-Wait a second.
-Uh...

167
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:22,833
You don’t know her? For real?

168
00:09:22,916 --> 00:09:24,583
Yeah.

169
00:09:24,666 --> 00:09:27,250
[sweeping]

170
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,333
-[sigh]
-[SUIGIN] It wasn’t a dream.

171
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:32,000
♪

172
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:34,416
[bubbling]

173
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:36,458
[groaning]

174
00:09:36,541 --> 00:09:38,291
[frantic mumbling]

175
00:09:38,375 --> 00:09:40,000
What do I do about this?!

176
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:42,500
-[yelling]
-[snoring]

177
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,041
♪

178
00:09:46,125 --> 00:09:48,666
[yelling]

179
00:09:48,750 --> 00:09:50,333
[growling, snarling]

180
00:09:51,708 --> 00:09:52,500
[grunt]

181
00:09:52,583 --> 00:09:55,291
[rumbling]

182
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:56,875
[panting]

183
00:09:56,958 --> 00:09:59,708
[roaring]

184
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:04,541
-Meow, meow!
-Ah!

185
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:06,708
[gasp]

186
00:10:06,791 --> 00:10:08,666
[roar]

187
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:09,791
[smash]

188
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:12,250
[grunt]

189
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:13,750
[sigh]

190
00:10:13,833 --> 00:10:16,791
♪

191
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:18,708
[growling]

192
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:26,791
Thousand Graves... arise!

193
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:28,791
[energy sizzling]

194
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:31,791
[rocks crumbling]

195
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:37,291
[tombstones rumbling]

196
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,250
[growling]

197
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:43,583
[tombstones rumbling]

198
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:47,541
[roaring]

199
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:49,083
[crash]

200
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:53,750
-[pained grunt]
-[smash]

201
00:10:58,375 --> 00:11:00,208
♪

202
00:11:00,291 --> 00:11:01,416
Meow meow!

203
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:04,416
It’s okay. I’m not losing this.

204
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:08,000
[growling]

205
00:11:09,166 --> 00:11:10,500
[flapping]

206
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:11,500
That’s right.

207
00:11:12,458 --> 00:11:13,625
I’ll win.

208
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:16,208
I have to protect this world.

209
00:11:16,291 --> 00:11:17,625
Protect you.

210
00:11:17,708 --> 00:11:19,625
So, I’ll keep fighting,

211
00:11:19,708 --> 00:11:21,416
for as long as it takes.

212
00:11:22,791 --> 00:11:24,958
[air rushing]

213
00:11:25,041 --> 00:11:27,500
Then, one day, when it’s over...

214
00:11:27,583 --> 00:11:31,791
[screaming]

215
00:11:38,958 --> 00:11:40,750
That’s when...

216
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,083
I’ll see you again.

217
00:13:15,416 --> 00:13:18,083
[SUIGIN]
The Silver Guardian!

